A few things that got me out of bed early at the end of 2022. 

Rhinos are a symbol of good luck in many cultures. That I came this close to one (twice!), I’ll take as a sign. 
It’s been a strange year for many of us. Here is to good things to come as we turn a calendar page. 
Sending love.

The most beautiful thing about life is that the things we think we know, we never fully understand until we go inward. Zegna, and Alessandro Sartori, are a consistent reminder of the depths to which we can better understand process, garments, and the humans who wear them. This house is rooted in sensitivity and play, and I’m lucky to have a seat at the table. 
Thank you @alessandrosartoriofficial and to the entire team @zegnaofficial for your magic and commitment to craft. It’s an honor to style your show. 
Thanks @ben_grimes_casting @danduran__ @jondefranc @me_morenaru and the entire cast of beautiful humans - those visible and not - who made this happen.

#zegna #mfw

My friend Phil waits for me to say hi to someone and snaps. It’s a funny game we play: my cluelessness to camera and genuine joy to see the people who stand behind them; Phil’s generous capturing of a moment, often mouth agape. I say he never misses my best side: my inner dork, my enthusiast, my naive fashion nomad. This is a @mrstreetpeeper appreciation post.
